      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When it comes to dressing for a boardroom meeting, it's all about exuding confidence and respect for the executives. For men, a well-fitted suit in a neutral color, a crisp white shirt, and a simple yet elegant watch are must-haves. Avoid anything too flashy or trendy, and make sure your hair is clean and styled neatly. For women, a tailored pantsuit or a professional dress in a conservative color palette is ideal, and don't forget to keep jewelry to a minimum. And let's be real, a good pair of heels can make all the difference in commanding respect.",
